{"id": 3924, "title": "Ticket #3924: Binary EC2 user data not handled properly", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen a user provides EC2 instance data via a file, the data can be binary. But the ec2_gahp handles the file contents as a NUL-terminated ascii string, leading to data loss for binary data.\n\n<p>The function <code>readShortFile()</code> should use the <code>string::assign()</code> method that takes a pointer and a length to copy the file contents into the <code>contents</code> variable.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2013-Oct-07 12:49:30 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong> Looks good.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Oct-14 14:55</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=37840\">[37840]</a></span>: edit 8.0.4 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3924\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3924'); return false;\" title=\"Binary EC2 user data not handled properly\">#3924</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Oct-07 13:31</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=37788\">[37788]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3924\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3924'); return false;\" title=\"Binary EC2 user data not handled properly\">#3924</a></span>) Document fix for binary user data files.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Oct-07 11:53</td>\n<td align=